com.googlecode.jctree

Class MapIndexedArrayListTree<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.googlecode.jctree.MapIndexedArrayListTree<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E -
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Tree<E>, java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Iterable<E>, java.util.Collection<E>

    public class MapIndexedArrayListTree<E>
extends java.lang.Object
implements Tree<E>, java.lang.Cloneable
    This is a general purpose tree where each node is free to have any number of children This implementation of tree interface is done using ArrayListas underlying data structure. As a result, children are maintained in insertion order under their respective parents
    Author:
    Gaurav Saxena
